9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 433, L.D. 1016, “An Act to Establish the
10 Manufactured Housing Community and Mobile Home Park Preservation and Assistance
11 Fund”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 10 MRSA §9090-A is enacted to read:
15 §9090-A. Transfer assessment
16 1. Fee payment required. Beginning January 1, 2026, the purchaser of a
17 manufactured housing community shall pay to the registry of deeds of the county where all
18 or a majority of the acreage of the purchased real property associated with the manufactured
19 housing community is located a fee equal to $10,000 for each manufactured housing
20 community lot in the manufactured housing community. The money must be paid to the
21 registry of deeds when the deed of the manufactured housing community is offered for
22 recordation.
23 2. Exceptions. The following entities are not required to pay the fee under subsection
24 1:
25 A. The Maine State Housing Authority;
26 B. A municipal housing authority as defined in Title 30-A, section 4702, subsection
27 10-A;
28 C. A cooperative or other entity in which membership is limited to manufactured home
29 owners; and
30 D. Entities that have a net worth of less than $50,000,000.
31 3. Evidence of payment; disposition of fee. Evidence of the fee payment under
32 subsection 1 or an exception to the fee requirement under subsection 2 must be retained by
33 the registry of deeds of the county where all or a majority of the acreage of the purchased
34 real property associated with the manufactured housing community is located in a manner
