315 established by the register of deeds. The register of deeds shall, on or before the 10th day
326 of each month, pay to the Treasurer of State 95% of the fee collected pursuant to this section
337 during the previous month. The remaining 5% must be retained for the county by the
348 register of deeds and accounted for to the county treasurer as reimbursement for services
359 rendered by the registry of deeds in collecting the fee.
6 4. Distribution of State's share of proceeds. The Treasurer of State shall credit all
7 fees received pursuant to this section to the Manufactured Housing Community and Mobile
8 Home Park Preservation and Assistance Fund established in Title 30-A, section 4754-B.
9 Sec. 2. 10 MRSA §9094-B is enacted to read:
10 §9094-B. Transfer assessment
11 1. Fee payment required. Beginning January 1, 2026, the purchaser of a mobile
12 home park shall pay to the registry of deeds of the county where all or a majority of the
13 acreage of the mobile home park is located a fee equal to $10,000 for each mobile home
14 park lot within the mobile home park. The money must be paid to the registry of deeds
15 when the deed of the mobile home park is offered for recordation.
16 2. Exceptions. The following entities are not required to pay the fee under subsection
17 1:
18 A. The Maine State Housing Authority;
19 B. A municipal housing authority as defined in Title 30-A, section 4702, subsection
20 10-A;
21 C. A cooperative or other entity in which membership is limited to mobile home
22 owners; and
23 D. Entities that have a net worth of less than $50,000,000.
24 3. Evidence of payment; disposition of fee. Evidence of the fee payment under
25 subsection 1 or an exception to the fee requirement under subsection 2 must be retained by
26 the registry of deeds of the county where all or a majority of the acreage of the mobile
27 home park is located in a manner established by the register of deeds. The register of deeds
28 shall, on or before the 10th day of each month, pay to the Treasurer of State 95% of the
29 fees collected pursuant to this section during the previous month. The remaining 5% must
30 be retained for the county by the register of deeds and accounted for to the county treasurer
31 as reimbursement for services rendered by the county in collecting the fee.
32 4. Distribution of State's share of proceeds. The Treasurer of State shall credit all
33 fees received pursuant to this section to the Manufactured Housing Community and Mobile
34 Home Park Preservation and Assistance Fund established in Title 30-A, section 4754-B.
35 Sec. 3. 30-A MRSA §4754-B is enacted to read:
36 §4754-B. Manufactured Housing Community and Mobile Home Park Preservation
37 and Assistance Fund
38 The Manufactured Housing Community and Mobile Home Park Preservation and
39 Assistance Fund, referred to in this section as "the fund," is established within the Maine
40 State Housing Authority as a nonlapsing, dedicated fund to be administered for the
41 purposes described in subsection 1.
Page 2 - 132LR2156(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 433, L.D. 1016
1 1. Purpose. The Maine State Housing Authority shall administer the fund to maintain
2 housing affordability in manufactured housing communities and mobile home parks,
3 regulated by Title 10, chapter 951, subchapter 6 and chapter 953, respectively, to support
4 ownership of manufactured housing communities and mobile home parks by homeowners,
5 homeowners' associations, resident-owned housing cooperatives or other nonprofit entities
6 representing the interests of homeowners in manufactured housing communities or mobile
7 home parks.
8 2. Source of funds. The Treasurer of State shall transfer to the fund the money
9 collected under Title 10, sections 9090-A and 9094-B. The fund may accept revenue from
10 grants, bequests, gifts or contributions from any source, public or private, including any
11 sums that may be appropriated by the Legislature, transferred to the fund from time to time
12 by the Treasurer of State or dedicated to the fund pursuant to law.
13 Sec. 4. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
14 allocations are made.
15 HOUSING AUTHORITY, MAINE STATE
16 Manufactured Housing Community and Mobile Home Park Preservation and
17 Assistance Fund N523
18 Initiative: Provides base allocations to authorize expenditures to support ownership of
19 manufactured housing communities and mobile home parks by owners of manufactured
20 homes and mobile homes.
21 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
22 All Other $500 $500
23 __________ __________
24 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $500 $500
